## Feature Design: Minimal, Extensible

### 1. AI Insights Checkbox (Job Template Level)

When enabled, AAP automatically:
- Captures job failure context (stdout, stderr, task details, inventory host vars)
- Sends structured prompt to configured AI endpoint
- Parses AI response
- Displays insights in job output
- Optionally creates remediation job template

### 2. Structured Prompt to AI (Auto-Generated)

AAP constructs a prompt like:

```json
{
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "system",
      "content": "You are an expert Ansible automation troubleshooter. Analyze failures and provide: 1) Root cause in plain English, 2) Affected component details, 3) Step-by-step remediation"
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Job Template: Install PostgreSQL\nPlaybook: install_pgsql.yml\nTask: Install PostgreSQL\nHost: server01 (RHEL 9.3)\nError: Failed to download metadata for repo 'rhel-9-for-x86_64-baseos-rpms'\nFull Output: [task output here]\nHost Variables: ansible_distribution=RedHat, ansible_distribution_version=9.3"
    }
  ]
}
```

### 3. AI Response Parsing

AI returns structured or semi-structured insights:

```json
{
  "root_cause": "Repository not enabled or subscription issue",
  "affected_component": "server01 RHEL subscription",
  "remediation_steps": [
    "Check subscription status",
    "Enable repository",
    "Re-run playbook"
  ],
  "remediation_playbook": "---\n- name: Fix subscription\n  hosts: server01\n  tasks:\n    - name: Enable repo\n      command: subscription-manager repos --enable=rhel-9-for-x86_64-baseos-rpms"
}
```

AAP displays this in the job output UI (similar to how you show stdout now).

